definition.value: Treatment with a neuromuscular blocking agent and inhibitor of acetyl choline release at motor terminals. It can be used to treat certain ailments like cervical dystonia and sialorrhea.

value.value: Treatment with Botulinum toxin,  a neurotoxic protein which blocks release of acetylcholine at neuromuscular junctions causing muscle paralysis. This therapy has many therapeutic uses including chronic migraine, spastic disorders, cervical dystonia, and detrusor hyperactivity.

definition.value: Treatment with Botulinum toxin type A which can treat certain conditions. Currently it is used to smoothed wrinkles. It is also called Botox treatment.
A set of tests or assessments to determine congnitive abilities of a patient.

value.value: Evaluation for cognitive impairment by assessing the neuropsychological domains.
Evaluation of patient's cominucation involving naming, reading, writing, and repeating words.
Evaluation of organizing and planning ability, as well as working memory, mental flexibility, list-making, and execution of tasks.
Evaluation of a patient's ability to analyze information, detect patterns, detect relationships, or problem solveing abilities on an intangible  level.
Evaluation of short-term and long-term emory in a patient.

definition.value: Evaluation of a patient's concentration or attention to a prompt or test.

value.value: Evaluation of a person’s ability to conceptualize and manipulate two- and three-dimensional objects.

Surgical implantation of a device for the treatment of severe to profound sensorineural hearing loss. It works by transducing acoustic energy into an electrical signal, which is used to stimulate surviving spiral ganglion cells of the auditory nerve.

definition.value: A procedure where a substance or object is inserted into the body.
A procedure to place an electrode in some part of the body for therapeutic purposes.

value.value: The surgical implantation of a central neural auditory prosthesis for treatment of profound sensorinerual hearing loss in patients who are not cochlear implant candidates due to a lack of anatomically intact cochlear nerves or implantable cochleae.

definition.value: Treatment to improve hearing.
Use of hearing aids to improve hearing.
Assessment and management of hearing loss.
Hearing therapy to help children born with hearing loss that have not learned to listen and talk.
A medical device inserted into the body to help control or monitor the heart and/or cardiovascular system.

value.value: Surgical insertion of an adjustable artificial electrical pulse generators into the body to interrogate and control the he pacing rate, the pulse width, and the voltage in order to a person's heart function.
Insertion of a pacemaker that attaches one lead to the upper or lower heart chamber.
The implantation of a pacemaker that uses two leads, one for the upper and one for lower chamber of the heart.
Surgical insertion of a pacemaker that is used in cardiac resynchronization therapy.

definition.value: Expandable tubular metallic devices inserted into coronary arteries.
Insertion of a medical device that delivers fluids, such as nutrients and medications, into a patient's body in controlled amounts.
Insertion of a continuous subcutaneous insulin infusion to regulate insulin levels in a patient.

value.value: A therapy used in patients with type 1 diabetes mellitus (T1DM) to improve glucose control and/or reduce the risk of hypoglycaemia.

definition.value: Use of a medical device that delivers fluids, such as nutrients and medications, into a patient's body in controlled amounts.

label.value: cataract extraction with intraocular lens insertion

definition.value: Surgical removal of the opacified lens and implantation of an artificial intraocular lens (IOL).

definition.value: Surgical incision into the eardrum to relieve pressure or drain fluid with placement of tympanostomy tubes to allow fluid to pass through the ear canal into the middle ear.

Surgical procedure to replace the weight-bearing surfaces of the knee joint.

value.value: A reconstructive proceder that surgically replaces the hip joint with an artificial prosthesis.

definition.value: Placement of a intrauterine contraceptive device that prevents pregnancy.
Surgical removal of a mass without cutting into or dissecting it.
Surgical procedure that involves removal of the entire globe and its intraocular contents, with preservation of all other periorbital and orbital structures.
Surgical removal of tumor cells without removing surrounding tissue or organs.

value.value: A procedure that uses very small amounts of radioactive materials to examine organ function and structure.
